All file:line refs are as of this date ƒ?" verify against current source before acting.

## The bug (what we're hunting)
Certain skinned NPC meshes render ~10-30 **contiguous TAIL** vertices flung to a stale-looking **WORLD-space** position (`[-2816,0,-6400]`, Y=0), while the bulk is correct. **D3D11-only** (D3D9/gl05 clean, same mesh).
PROVEN: (a) skinning OUTPUT is sane ƒ?" systemStream has no spike (`cape-skin-spike.txt` empty for the soft path); (b) the dynamic VB the GPU reads HAS the spike (`cape-dynvb-outlier.txt`: numVerts=1692 outliers=27 firstIdx=1665; numVerts=2691 outliers=10); (c) the copy writes every vert (sentinel: 387/387 full, 0 underwrite); (d) bone indices are all in range (clamp caught 0 OOB). ƒØ' **The spike enters AFTER skinning, in the D3D11 dynamic-VB / draw layer.**

## Leaf path for the spike mesh (both trees agree)
