NOTE on coordinate space: both traces say CPU soft/hard fill writes OBJECT space (model-to-root via `getBindPoseModelToRootTransforms`, SBSSP.cpp:563); world transform is applied by the VS cbuffer (`setObjectToWorldTransformAndScale` SBSSP.cpp:491), NOT in the VB. **A WORLD-space dynamic VB is therefore NOT a normal fill output ƒ+' it implicates stale-ring / read-past / wrong-slice, i.e. the GPU fetching bytes the fill never wrote.** (Open thread: confirm the spike mesh's fill space directly ƒ?" fillVertexBufferHard is not yet instrumented.)

