The bind path has two cases: a single VB binds offset 0 and folds the dynamic slice into `BaseVertexIndex`; a VB vector can bind a byte offset when stream offsets are supported. I’m checking which path `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` constructs for D3D9 soft-skin and how the render commands are generated.
