942-/**
943- * Calculate the bounding box coordinates for this blended mesh.
944- *
945- * Since this instance represents a mesh that is modified by transforms,
946- * the bounding box will necessarily change when the transforms change.
947- * Therefore, it makes no sense for this instance to try to cache this
948- * data internally.  Users of this class that want a cheap bounding box
949- * calculation will need to be smart about (1) how accurate the bounding
950- * box must be and (2) how often they need to run over this data to
951- * caculate it.
952- *
953- * Performance side-effects: this function will force the skeleton to evaluate 
954- * its transforms if that event hasn't already happened.
955- *
956- * @param minVector  the minimum x, y and z value for the bounding box
957- *                   are returned in this vector.
958- * @param maxVector  the maximum x, y and z value for the bounding box
959- *                   are returned in this vector.
960- */
