.planning\handoff\2026-06-07-cape-spike-LIVE-ONLY-undefined-memory-reframe.md:65:DECISIVE NEXT READ: does `cape-trace-systemstream.txt` have an SS-SPIKE for numVerts=1692/2691? YES→ hard fill is source (instrument fillVertexBufferHard SSE @2305). NO→ pure D3D11 ring/offset; B's ring/discard/lockOff fields localize it (then W2/W3/W4: verify bind-offset==write-pointer, read-past with real draw counts, diff D3D9 live).
.planning\handoff\2026-06-07-cape-spike-LIVE-ONLY-undefined-memory-reframe.md:132:- **Cursor 30** (`CONSULT-30-cursor.out`): does the D3D11 input layout for the skeletal VS read a vertex component at an offset/stride the CPU skin never writes? (Position-at-0 clean but VS reads garbage elsewhere.) Byte-map of dynamic vertex: offset|component|written?|read?.
.planning\handoff\2026-06-07-cape-spike-LIVE-ONLY-undefined-memory-reframe.md:133:- **Codex 30** (`CONSULT-30-codex.out`): can a soft-skin draw fetch from an unwritten (undefined-since-DISCARD) ring region? Stride/offset consistency: `vertexSize` used for `m_offset`/bind vs the input-layout fetch stride.
.planning\handoff\2026-06-07-cape-spike-LIVE-ONLY-undefined-memory-reframe.md:137:- **Cursor 30** (`CONSULT-30-cursor.out`): NO unwritten declared vertex component. Single-stream `dynamicFormat` = position+normal(+color+UVs+dot3); `skinData` writes position/normal/dot3 each frame, `fillConstantVertexBufferData` writes color/2D-UVs once; copy is full-vertex memcpy → every declared byte populated at draw. Input-layout offsets/stride match engine exactly. VS uses POSITION-only for SV_Position. → REFUTES "VS reads an unwritten component." Points to **index read-past (whole stale vertices)** or **"GPU sees different memory than the CPU staging read"** (coherency/ring-timing).
.planning\handoff\2026-06-07-cape-spike-LIVE-ONLY-undefined-memory-reframe.md:138:- **Codex 30** (`CONSULT-30-codex.out`): the ONLY viable read-past = **index value >= written vertex count** (stride, `m_offset`/bind byte math, and `BaseVertexLocation=0` all verified correct; no offset-lifetime/stale-binding issue). 
.planning\handoff\2026-06-07-cape-spike-LIVE-ONLY-undefined-memory-reframe.md:143:Top ranks recycled already-killed ideas (strip=dormant, multi-stream=off, systemStream-uninit would be captured-not-zeroed). Two FRESH + fitting: **(Rank 5) STALE CACHED InputLayout stride mismatch** — IA stride 48 vs a cached layout expecting 32 → verts read N bytes off, position-at-0 still correct (fits "position clean"); Cursor 30 only checked the CURRENT format, not a stale cached layout — WORTH CHECKING the input-layout cache key/stride at garment draws. **(Rank 7) `getRingBuffer()` NULL-fallback to MAIN ring** if a garment binds before its first lock (m_ringBuffer==nullptr) — a risk introduced by the 16MB skin-ring split; reverting the skin ring removes it. Full: `CONSULT-30-SONNET-lateral.out`.
.planning\handoff\2026-06-07-cape-spike-LIVE-ONLY-undefined-memory-reframe.md:146:**The VS input layout reads vertex bytes the skin path never writes** (a declared-but-unwritten component — tangent/binormal/dot3 set, 2nd texcoord, or a stride/offset mismatch), so position-at-0 reads clean but the VS consumes uninitialized bytes → garbage live, zero replay. OR an under-write (skin writes M < draw's N). The memset test + Cursor 30 byte-map decide between them.
.planning\milestones\v2.0-ROADMAP.md:116:  - [x] 11-09.9-PLAN.md — TACTICAL sub-plan: TF_RGB_888 lock-bridge for 24bpp-engine-fill -> 32bpp-DXGI-storage. **Closed 2026-05-21 at 1-iteration milestone — terrain-load FATAL gone; engine fully loads Tatooine.** Direct3d11_TextureData::lock no longer FATALs on TF_RGB_888 (TextureFormat 4): bridge case allocates a CPU shadow at 24bpp engine stride during lock; unlock allocates a USAGE_STAGING texture at m_destFormat (DXGI BGRX/BGRA), expands row-by-row with straight 3→4 byte copy + 0xFF in byte 3 (TF_RGB_888 memory order is BGR per TextureFormatInfo masks — matches DXGI BGRX/BGRA byte order, no channel swap needed), CopySubresourceRegions to destination subresource, and releases. Defensive FATALs for unsupported bridge cases (cube/volume, read-only, non-TF_RGB_888 source, RGBA-ordered DXGI destination) with clear "Plan 11-09.10 territory" markers. Smoke verified: terrain texture load completes; crash dump shows `Terrain: terrain/tatooine.trn` + `Player: 3500.48 5.53 -4979.23` (in-world Tatooine coords). Plan 11-09 + 11-09.5/6/7/8 milestones preserved. Next blocker discovered in a DIFFERENT category: scaffold_fatal_stub FATAL on `Graphics::setPointSize` (Graphics.cpp:832) from `StarAppearance::LocalShaderPrimitive::draw` (StarAppearance.cpp:337); confirmed via Direct3d11.cpp:617-622 — setPointSize / setPointSizeMax / setPointSizeMin / setPointScaleEnable / setPointScaleFactor / setPointSpriteEnable all still Plan 11-02 STUB scaffolds; design intent comment at lines 613-616 already says these should be no-ops in D3D11 (fixed-function point-sprite control was dropped from D3D10+). Inherited by Plan 11-09.10. Commits: `39d340a40` (Iter-1). — requirements D3D11-02
.planning\milestones\v2.0-ROADMAP.md:119:  - [x] 11-09.12-PLAN.md — TACTICAL sub-plan: defensive session-only audit of stage/d3d11-debug.log; surfaced one concrete real-bug verdict + applied surgical fix. **Closed 2026-05-22 at 1-iteration milestone — debug-layer ERROR rate dropped 152,870→2 per session (99.9987% reduction); visible geometry now correctly rasterized.** Audit found 152,869 id=366 ERRORs ("Vertex Buffer Offset (N) at input vertex slot 0 not aligned to (4)") with N = raw vertex index across hundreds of non-4-aligned values + 1 id=281 CopySubresource format-mismatch one-shot. Root cause: `Direct3d11_StateCache::setVertexBuffer` line 1038 was passing `data->getOffset()` (a VERTEX INDEX per `Direct3d11_DynamicVertexBufferData.cpp:234`) directly to `IASetVertexBuffers` as a BYTE offset. Multi-stream path at `Direct3d11_VertexBufferVectorData.cpp:145` correctly did `* strides[stream]`; single-stream was missing the conversion. Fix: one-line `ms_currentVBOffset = data->getOffset() * ms_currentVBStride;` Smoke verified (Kenny ~07:55): wildly-flickering geometry → stable triangles confined to actual real-geometry submission area; magenta-over-black state now ISOLATED from any alignment artifacts (pure Plan 11-05 PEXE rejection). Plan 11-09 + 11-09.5/6/7/8/9/10/11 milestones preserved. Audit document: 11-09.12-AUDIT.md. Next blocker: textured-passthrough fallback PS (replace magenta hardcode with texture-slot-0 sample). Inherited by Plan 11-09.13. Commits: `6100e469a` (Iter-1). — requirements D3D11-02
.planning\milestones\v2.0-ROADMAP.md:123:  - [x] 11-09.8-PLAN.md — TACTICAL sub-plan: reflection-driven input-layout assembly + phantom zero buffer at slot 15 (CODEX-reviewed C-lite/A2 hybrid). **Closed 2026-05-21 at 1-iteration milestone — CODEX Q6 acceptance bar FULLY MET.** D3DReflect post-compile captures VS input signatures (SV_* filtered); install-time 16-byte zero-filled BIND_VERTEX_BUFFER at slot 15; Direct3d11_VertexBufferDescriptorMap::augmentWithPhantomElements appends missing semantics; Direct3d11_VertexDeclarationMap calls augment in both single-stream + multi-stream paths; Direct3d11_StateCache::applyPreDrawState binds phantom buffer at slot 15 unconditionally before draws. Smoke verified: stage/d3d11-debug.log session-only shows **0 [ERROR] / 0 [WARNING]** (TEXCOORD2 cascade fully resolved; 28,761 historic count was append-log noise); **c0000005 access violation on hair_s40 GONE** (CODEX Q5a confirmed -- same root cause). Engine progressed dramatically: UpTime 50 / MainLoop 5568 (Plan 11-09.7) → UpTime 73 / MainLoop 7649 (Plan 11-09.8), Tatooine terrain load reached. Plan 11-09 + 11-09.5 + 11-09.6 + 11-09.7 milestones preserved. Next blocker discovered: FATAL on Direct3d11_TextureData::lock for TF_RGB_888 (TextureFormat enum value 4 = 24bpp RGB; Plan 11-04 translation table at Direct3d11_TextureData.cpp:62 maps to DXGI_FORMAT_UNKNOWN per "engine promotes via runtimeFormats" comment; promotion not firing for terrain textures). Inherited by Plan 11-09.9. Commits: _(close hash pending)_. CODEX consult preserved at 11-09.8-CODEX-CONSULT-texcoord2-signature-mismatch.md. — requirements D3D11-02, D3D11-03 Triggered by Plan 11-09.7 close smoke: 20+ D3D11 debug-layer ERRORs on CreateInputLayout missing TEXCOORD/2 (vs_4_0 strictness preserves declared VS inputs even when unused; engine VBFormat doesn't fabricate missing semantics). CODEX consult endorsed reflection-driven layout assembly + phantom zero-buffer pad over HLSL stripping / shader-model rollback / hardcoded fixes. Architecture: D3DReflect each VS bytecode post-compile to capture input signature (filter SV_*); install-time 16-byte zero-filled BIND_VERTEX_BUFFER as phantom slot 15 buffer; VertexBufferDescriptorMap augments format-derived elements with phantom InputSlot=15 entries for missing non-SV semantics; StateCache binds phantom buffer at slot 15 with stride=0 before every draw. Per CODEX Q5 the c0000005 access violation (hair_s40 load) is NOT assumed to share root cause; will resolve OR scope to Iter-2 with real stack capture. Iteration target: 1. Risk profile: zero BSOD (pure CPU + 1 install-time GPU buffer). autonomous:false; Kenny smoke validates avatar geometry visible. CODEX consult preserved at 11-09.8-CODEX-CONSULT-texcoord2-signature-mismatch.md. — requirements D3D11-02, D3D11-03
