.planning\research\CONSULT-35-codex-d3d9-softskin-reference-spec.txt:6:- Trustworthy in-process facts: the CPU skin output (systemStream) is OBJECT-space and tight/clean (ss-tight, maxDist=3); the D3D11 written VB slice has NO position outliers in [0, writtenCount) (sentinel-aware centroid scan); copyN==lockN==m_vertexCount (structural); the dynamic-ring lifetime is FALSIFIED (16MB never-wrap ring AND no-skin-ring-at-all both still spike). So the bytes the fill WROTE are clean — yet the GPU draws displaced geometry => the GPU fetches vertex bytes OUTSIDE the written [0,writtenCount) region, or at a wrong base/stride/offset.
