codex
The lock/write counts are source-tied: `m_vertexCount` comes from the mesh, the `SystemVertexBuffer` is constructed with that same count, and the dynamic copy count asks that system buffer for its stored count. That means the intended D3D9 soft-skin copy writes the full locked slice; the draw range can be narrower per primitive because render commands use per-primitive index min/max.
